# Android SDK Conventions

## Tech Stack

Kotlin, OpenTelemetry Android SDK, Gradle, min API 21

## Instrumentation Pattern

Each instrumentation lives in `instrumentation/` as a self-contained module:
- Activity lifecycle
- Fragment lifecycle
- ANR detection
- Crash reporting
- Network (OkHttp)
- Screen rendering

## Span Attributes

Use `pulse.*` prefixed attributes for Pulse-specific data:
- `pulse.type` — categorizes the span (interaction, screen, network, etc.)
- `pulse.interaction.name` — critical interaction name
- `pulse.screen.name` — screen identifier

## Resource Attributes

- `app.version`, `os.type`, `os.version`, `device.model.name`

## Publishing

Automated via `.github/workflows/publish-android.yml`

## Code Style

Follow Kotlin conventions — `camelCase` for functions/properties, `PascalCase` for classes.
